=== PRIORITY 1: VISION MODEL — Photo-based Food Logging ===

Implement Qwen3-VL-2B vision model support for photo-based food logging.
This is the PRIMARY focus of this session.

Steps:
1. Research how llama.cpp handles vision models (llava-style API)
   - Look at llama.cpp examples/llava/ for the C API usage
   - Understand: llava_image_embed_make_with_bytes, clip_model_load, etc.
   - Check if our source-built xcframework (b7310) includes the vision/clip headers
   - If not, rebuild xcframework with vision support enabled

2. Implement vision pipeline in LlamaCppBackend:
   - Load mmproj (multimodal projector) alongside the main model
   - Add method: processImage(UIImage) -> image embeddings
   - Add method: respondWithImage(prompt, image) -> text response
   - Keep existing text-only respond() working

3. Download and test Qwen3-VL-2B model:
   - Files already on GitHub releases: Qwen3-VL-2B-Instruct-Q4_K_M.gguf + mmproj
   - Update AIModelTier to include a vision tier
   - Test on simulator first, then verify it works

4. Add photo food logging UI:
   - Camera button in AI chat (already have supportsVision flag)
   - Take photo or pick from gallery
   - Send to vision model: "What food is in this image? Estimate calories."
   - Parse response → open food log sheet pre-filled
   - Show the image in the chat bubble

5. Add nutrition label scanning via vision:
   - Photo of nutrition label → vision model extracts macros
   - Pre-fill the quick add form with extracted values

6. Test extensively:
   - Photo of an egg → should identify as egg
   - Photo of a plate of food → should list items
   - Photo of nutrition label → should extract calories/protein/carbs/fat
   - Dark/blurry photos → should say "can't identify"

=== PRIORITY 2: CONTINUE AI CHAT QUALITY ===

While vision work is in progress, also improve:
- Multi-turn conversation flow
- Test with eval harness after any changes
- Fix any bugs found during testing

=== PRIORITY 3: INFERENCE SPEED ===

- The Metal GPU shader bug is in llama.cpp's source code (bfloat/half mismatch)
- Check if newer llama.cpp (b8000+) has fixed this
- If fixed, rebuild xcframework and enable GPU
- Also try building with GGML_METAL_USE_BF16=OFF to disable bfloat

=== HOW TO WORK ===

- Check .claude-stop status before every cycle
- Commit after each meaningful improvement
- Run tests after every change
- Build after every change
- Push to git frequently
- When stuck on vision API, search llama.cpp source code and examples
- If vision doesn't work with b7310, try building latest llama.cpp

Status options:
- RUNNING: continue the loop
- STOP: finish current work, commit, halt
- PAUSE: commit and wait for instructions
- REDIRECT: read Direction field, apply changes, set back to RUNNING
